"oh, no," she quickly replied. "This one is for Hera. You shall have to drag your own prey home." She laughed and gazed back out the entrance.  Sin knew Hera would sense and know that she had that which she was sent to hunt.  But, now was time to hide Maia.  Until Hera called.  <br>
The great male lion lay down near the entrance and Sin walked over to join him.  She lay back down to rest against him as the sun began to set.  It had been a long day carrying the pleiade to the cave of lions. <br>
She looked back at Maia.  Now she just had to wait for Hera.<br>
